<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Demo_Using_Excel">Demo Using Excel</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>How to download historical data from Yahoo</li>
<li>How to manipulate it in Excel</li>
<li>How to compute the metrics weâ€™ve been talking about</li>
</ul>
<h1> <span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span></h1>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Download_historical_data">Download historical data</span></h2>
<p>There are lots of good sources of financial data online. Both Yahoo Finance <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://finance.yahoo.com/">[1]</a> and Google Finance <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.google.com/finance">[2]</a> provide historical prices.
<ul><li> For example, Apple on <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://finance.yahoo.com/q?s=AAPL&amp;ql=0">Yahoo</a> and <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.google.com/finance?q=NASDAQ%3AAAPL&amp;ei=eFeKUNjoGYeHwAORXg">Google</a>
</li><li> Historic data can be saved as csv eg. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://finance.yahoo.com/q/hp?s=AAPL&amp;a=00&amp;b=1&amp;c=2011&amp;d=11&amp;e=31&amp;f=2011&amp;g=d">Yahoo - Apple 2011 csv</a> and <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.google.com/finance/historical?cid=22144&amp;startdate=Jan+1%2C+2011&amp;enddate=dec+31%2C+2011&amp;num=30&amp;ei=KFmKUJiGJYeHwAORXg">Google - Apple 2011 csv</a>
</li><li> This data can be imported into excel or other spreadsheet programs
<ul><li> The data includes date, open, high, low, close, volume, and adjusted close.
</li><li> The data we will work with is adjusted close. Adjusted close is different from close.</p>
</li></ul>
</li></ul>

<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="How_to_manipulate_it_in_Excel">How to manipulate it in Excel</span></h2>
<p>How to calculate values using real data in a spread sheet.</p>
<ul>
<li>Sort data by date ascending (oldest first)</li>
<li>Delete open, high, low, close, and volume, leaving date and adjusted close.</li>
<li>Calculate Total Return (Annual Return)
<ul><li><ul><li> (Final Value/First Value)-1, for example =(D253/D2)-1</li>
</li></ul>
</li></ul>
<li>Calculate Daily Return
<ul><li><ul><li> (Today's value/Yesterday's Value)-1, for example =(B3/B2)-1
</li><li> Format as percentage.</li>
</li></ul>
</li></ul>
<li>Calculate Average Daily Return.
<ul><li><ul><li> Average of all Daily Returns, for example =average(C2:C253)
</li><li> Format as number.</li>
</li></ul>
</li></ul>
<li>Calculate Standard Deviation of Daily Return.
<ul><li><ul><li> Standard Deviation over all Daily Returns, for example =stdev(C2:C253)
</li><li> Format as number</li>
</li></ul>
</li></ul>
<li>Calculate Sharpe Ratio
<ul><li><ul><li> Square Root of 253 multiplied by (Average Daily Return divided by Standard Deviation of Daily Returns), for example =sqrt(253)*F4/F5</li>
</li></ul>
</li></ul>
</ul>
<p></p>

